{
  "texts": [
    "However, there is an essential difference between wave-based crack detection and image semantic segmentation, i.e., the spatial mismatch between input and output.",
    "The ultimate aim of a crack detection model is to use the data from the sparsely distributed sensor array to make dense predictions for the solid domain.",
    "Though regularly distributed sensor arrays imply locational information in the data, they can not be easily related to the spatial locations of the output.",
    "The spatial dimension of sensors (sparse) is mismatched with the desired spatial dimension of crack predictions (dense).",
    "Besides, the measured wavefield also involves temporal dimension and x-/y-displacements instead of image channels."
  ]
}